## COMPONENT BEHAVIOR RULES

### IdeaChat.tsx

- Uses Vercel AI SDK `useChat` hook
- Streams responses in real-time
- Detects `<REFINED_IDEA>` tag in stream and auto-advances to outline stage
- Saves conversation history to `books.idea_conversation` on each turn
- Has a "Skip refinement, I know my idea" button that shows a form

### OutlineEditor.tsx

- Renders chapters as draggable cards using @dnd-kit/sortable
- Each card is inline-editable (click title or description to edit)
- "Add Chapter" button appends a new blank chapter
- "Regenerate Outline" button calls the outline API with current refined idea
- Large "Approve Outline & Start Writing" CTA button
- On approve: sets outline.approved = true, creates all chapter rows in DB with status 'pending'

### ChapterEditor.tsx

- Split view: left panel shows chapter list, right panel shows current chapter
- Uses a lightweight rich text editor (use TipTap)
- Toolbar: Bold, Italic, Heading, — and AI controls: "Regenerate", "Expand", "Rewrite Tone"
- Chapter status indicator (pending → generating → draft → edited). No per-chapter approval step.
- Auto-saves to Supabase every 30 seconds and on blur
- Any chapter with content (draft/edited) is automatically ready for export and used as prior-chapter context
- Word count shown per chapter and running total

### CoverGenerator.tsx

- Shows the book title and genre prominently
- "Generate Cover" button triggers DALL-E 3 call
- Shows generation spinner with a fun message ("Designing your cover…")
- Displays result as a large preview (book mockup frame around the image)
- "Regenerate" and "Download Cover" buttons
- Saves cover_url to books table

### ExportPanel.tsx

- Shows all chapters with checkmarks when all have content (draft/edited)
- "Compile & Download Book" button → calls /api/compile-book
- Downloads a .docx file with: cover page, table of contents, all chapters formatted
- Below the button: a formatted, step-by-step KDP publishing guide (static content, well-designed)
- KDP guide covers: account setup, manuscript formatting requirements, cover specs, pricing, categories, keywords

