## SUPABASE REALTIME

Enable Realtime on: `books`, `chapters` tables.

In ChapterEditor, subscribe to chapter updates so status changes reflect instantly.

In the dashboard, subscribe to books so word count and status update live.

Use the `useRealtime` hook in /hooks/useRealtime.ts for all subscriptions.

---

## ERROR HANDLING

- All async operations must use try/catch
- Show toast notifications (use sonner) for all errors and successes
- If chapter generation fails mid-stream, set chapter status back to 'pending' and show retry button
- If DALL-E fails, show fallback UI with a placeholder cover and "Try again" option
- Never show raw error messages to users — always use friendly copy

---

## AUTHENTICATION FLOW

- Supabase Auth with email/password + Google OAuth
- Protected routes: anything under /(dashboard) requires active session
- middleware.ts intercepts unauthenticated requests and redirects to /login
- On signup: auto-create profile row via Supabase trigger (create this trigger in migrations)
- On login: redirect to /dashboard

---

## STRIPE SUBSCRIPTION

- Free tier: up to 3 books, max 10 chapters per book
- Pro tier ($19/month): unlimited books, unlimited chapters, priority generation
- Show upgrade prompt when free tier limits are hit
- Webhook handler updates profiles.subscription_tier on subscription changes
- Use Stripe Customer Portal for subscription management

